212 §10A-17-2.07
213 (a) A decentralized unincorporated nonprofit
214 association is a legal entity separate from its members for
215 the purposes of determining and enforcing rights, duties, and
216 liabilities in contract and tort.
217 (b) A person is not liable for a breach of a
218 decentralized unincorporated nonprofit association's contract
219 merely because the person is a member, administrator,
220 authorized to participate in the management of the affairs of
221 the nonprofit association, or considered a member by the
222 nonprofit association.
223 (c) A person is not liable for a tortious act or
224 omission for which a decentralized unincorporated nonprofit
Page 8

omission for which a decentralized unincorporated nonprofit
SB277 Engrossed
225 association is liable merely because the person is a member or
226 administrator of the nonprofit association, authorized to
227 participate in the management of the affairs of the nonprofit
228 association, or considered a member by the nonprofit
229 association.
230 (d) A tortious act or omission of a member,
231 administrator, or other person for which a decentralized
232 unincorporated nonprofit association is liable is not imputed
233 to a person merely because the person is a member or
234 administrator of the nonprofit association, authorized to
235 participate in the management of the affairs of the nonprofit
236 association, or considered a member by the nonprofit
237 association.
238 (e) A member, administrator, person authorized to
239 participate in the management of the affairs of the nonprofit
240 association, or person considered a member by the nonprofit
241 association may assert a claim against the decentralized
242 unincorporated nonprofit association. A decentralized
243 unincorporated nonprofit association may assert a claim
244 against a member, administrator, person authorized to
245 participate in the management of the affairs of the nonprofit
246 association, or person considered a member by the nonprofit
247 association.
248 §10A-17-2.08
249 (a) A decentralized unincorporated nonprofit
250 association, in its own name, may institute, defend,
251 intervene, or participate in a judicial, administrative, or
252 other governmental proceeding or in an arbitration, mediation,
Page 9

other governmental proceeding or in an arbitration, mediation,
SB277 Engrossed
253 or any other form of alternative dispute resolution.
254 (b) A decentralized unincorporated nonprofit
255 association may assert a claim on behalf of its members if all
256 of the following apply:
257 (1) One or more members of the nonprofit association
258 have standing to assert a claim in their own right.
259 (2) The interests the nonprofit association seeks to
260 protect are germane to the nonprofit association's purposes.
261 (3) Neither the claim asserted, nor the relief
262 requested, requires the participation of a member.
263 §10A-17-2.09
264 A judgment or order against a decentralized
265 unincorporated nonprofit association is not by itself a
266 judgment or order against a member or administrator of the
267 nonprofit association.
