312 §10A-17-2.12
313 A claim for relief against a decentralized
314 unincorporated nonprofit association shall not abate merely
315 because of a change in its members or persons authorized to
316 administer the affairs of the nonprofit association.
317 §10A-17-2.13
318 Venue shall be:
319 (1) As provided in Section 6-3-6; or
320 (2) The county in which the agent authorized to receive
321 service of process under Section 10A-17-2.10 resides.
322 §10A-17-2.14
323 (a) A decentralized unincorporated nonprofit
324 association shall have perpetual existence unless its
325 governing principles otherwise specify.
326 (b) A decentralized unincorporated nonprofit
327 association may be dissolved as follows:
328 (1) If the governing principles of the nonprofit
329 association provide a time or method for dissolution, by that
330 method.
331 (2) If the governing principles of the nonprofit
332 association do not provide a method for dissolution, by
333 approval of its members pursuant to Section 10A-17-2.20.
334 (3) If membership in the decentralized unincorporated
335 nonprofit association falls below 100 members and the
336 decentralized unincorporated nonprofit association does not
Page 12

decentralized unincorporated nonprofit association does not
SB277 Engrossed
337 meet the requirements of Sections 10A-17-2.01 through
338 10A-17-2.15. In the event membership in the nonprofit
339 association falls below 100 members and the nonprofit
340 association meets the requirements of Sections 10A-17-2.01
341 through 10A-17-2.15, the entity shall automatically transition
342 to an Alabama unincorporated nonprofit association unless the
343 governing principles otherwise specify.
344 (4) By court order.
345 (c) After dissolution, a decentralized unincorporated
346 nonprofit association continues in existence until its
347 activities are wound up and terminated pursuant to Section
348 10A-17-2.26.
349 §10A-17-2.15
350 (a)(1) A person may become a member of a decentralized
351 unincorporated nonprofit association in accordance with the
352 governing principles of that decentralized unincorporated
353 nonprofit association.
354 (2) If there are no applicable governing principles, a
355 person shall be considered a member upon the purchase or
356 assumption of ownership of a membership interest.
357 (3) A person shall continue as a member absent the
358 person's suspension, dismissal, or expulsion pursuant to
359 subsection (b), resignation pursuant to Section 10A-17-2.16,
360 or the decentralized unincorporated nonprofit association's
