621 (3) If neither subdivision (1) or (2) applies, in
622 accordance with the law of unclaimed property contained in
623 Article 2A, Chapter 12 of Title 35, Code of Alabama 1975.
624 (c) In winding up a decentralized unincorporated
625 nonprofit association, the members may do all of the
626 following:
627 (1) Authorize an administrator to wind up the
628 decentralized unincorporated nonprofit association in
629 accordance with Section 10A-17-2.14. Any authorized
630 administrator shall owe the nonprofit association a duty of
631 care in the conduct or winding up of the decentralized
632 unincorporated nonprofit association to refrain from grossly
633 negligent or reckless conduct, willful or intentional
634 misconduct, or a knowing violation of the law.
635 (2) Preserve the decentralized unincorporated nonprofit
636 association's operations and property as a going concern for a
637 reasonable time.
638 (3) Prosecute and defend actions and proceedings,
639 whether civil, criminal, or administrative.
640 (4) Transfer the decentralized unincorporated nonprofit
641 association's property.
642 (5) Settle disputes by mediation or arbitration.
643 (6) Perform other acts necessary or appropriate to the
644 winding up.
