645 (d) If the members of a decentralized unincorporated
646 nonprofit association do not appoint an administrator or
647 administrators to wind up the decentralized unincorporated
648 nonprofit association, the members shall owe the decentralized
649 unincorporated nonprofit association a duty of care in the
650 conduct or winding up of the decentralized unincorporated
651 nonprofit association's operations to refrain from engaging in
652 grossly negligent or reckless conduct, willful or intentional
653 misconduct, or a knowing violation of the law.
654 §10A-17-2.27
655 A decentralized unincorporated nonprofit association
656 may effect a merger or conversion by complying with the
657 applicable provisions of Chapter 1 and its governing
658 principles.
659 §10A-17-2.28
660 Principles of law and equity supplement this chapter
661 unless displaced by a specific provision of this chapter.
